sinessinsider.com%2Fyoung-women-sober-curious-movement-bella-hadid-kin-ritual-2021-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esober%20curiosity%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20become%20louder%20and%20more%20open%20in%20recent%20years.%20Whereas%2020%20years%20ago%20a%20decision%20to%20abstain%20from%20alcohol%20was%20often%20kept%20hush-hush%20(the%20implication%20being%20that%20the%20abstainer%20had%20a%20shameful%20problem)%2C%20nowadays%20people%20are%20much%20more%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsober-celebrities-who-dont-drink-do-drugs%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eopen%20about%20sitting%20drinking%20out%3C%2Fa%3E.%20They're%20skipping%20happy%20hours%2C%20going%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-zers-are-leading-a-sober-dating-revolution-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebooze-free%20dates%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20laying%20out%20their%20reasoning%20for%20sobriety%20online.%20The%20beverage%20industry%20has%20been%20happy%20to%20cater%20to%20them%2C%20too.%20IWSR%2C%20which%20covers%20the%20alcoholic-beverage%20industry%2C%20said%20volume%20in%20the%20nonalcohol%20segment%20in%20the%20US%20grew%20by%2029%25%20in%202023%2C%20driven%20by%20young%20people%20in%20particular.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20everyone%20does%20a%20victory%20lap%20about%20how%20America's%20given%20up%20on%20alcohol%2C%20it's%20important%20to%20note%20that%20the%20nonalcohol%20segment%20is%20still%20pretty%20small%20%E2%80%94%20IWSR%20expects%20it%20to%20make%20up%204%25%20of%20the%20overall%20alcoholic-beverages%20market%20by%202027.%20And%20while%20the%20modern%20temperance%20movement%20is%20growing%2C%20so%20too%20is%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhard-seltzer-canned-cocktail-high-abv-beer-alcohol-drinks-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehigh-alcohol-content%20segment%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Americans%20are%20increasingly%20opting%20for%20spirits%20over%20beer%2C%20and%20ready-to-drink%20cocktails%20and%20high-ABV%20beers%20are%20becoming%20more%20popular%20than%20middle-of-the-road%20options.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPolling%20from%20Gallup%20suggests%20men%2C%20white%20people%2C%20college%20graduates%2C%20and%20higher-income%20people%20are%20among%20those%20with%20a%20higher%20propensity%20to%20drink.%20And%20heavy%20drinkers%20consume%20the%20bulk%20of%20alcohol%20volume%20in%20the%20US.%20But%20many%20drinkers%20are%20incorporating%20nonalcoholic%20options%20into%20their%20routines%20without%20giving%20up%20on%20booze%20altogether.%20They're%20looking%20at%20occasional%20abstention%20as%20a%20form%20of%20moderation.%20After%20all%2C%20per%20the%20market-research%20firm%20NIQ%2C%20more%20than%2093%25%20of%20nonalcohol%20buyers%20also%20buy%20alcoholic%20drinks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20people%20who%20are%20drinking%20a%20lot%20of%20NA%20stuff%2C%20they%20just%20are%20interested%20in%20more%20flavors%20and%20more%20beverage%20profiles%20and%20things%20like%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Dave%20Infante%2C%20a%20contributing%20editor%20and%20columnist%20at%20VinePair%20who%20writes%20a%20Substack%20about%20drinking%20called%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffingers.substack.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFingers%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BSo%20they're%20just%20drinking%20more%20interesting%20shit%20out%20of%20everything.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20some%20extent%2C%20drinking%20culture%20is%20moving%20toward%20the%20extremes.%20Sure%2C%20more%20people%20are%20abstaining%20on%20a%20given%20night%20%E2%80%94%20but%20when%20people%20do%20order%20an%20alcoholic%20drink%2C%20they're%20really%20going%20for%20it.%20They're%20getting%20an%20old-fashioned%2C%20not%20dialing%20down%20to%20a%20light%20beer%20or%20two.%20Instead%20of%20forgoing%20the%20real%20thing%20altogether%2C%20Negroni%20lovers%20are%20mixing%20in%20a%20phony%20Negroni%20from%20time%20to%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falcohol-cancer-risk-surgeon-general-report-smoking-cigarettes-obesity-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esurgeon%20general's%20recent%20warning%20that%20alcohol%20can%20cause%20cancer%3C%2Fa%3E%20reiterated%20for%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20something%20they%20already%20(begrudgingly)%20knew%3A%20Drinking%20is%20not%20good%20for%20you.%20The%20proportion%20of%20Americans%20who%20say%20drinking%20is%20bad%20for%20health%20has%20risen%20quite%20steadily%20over%20the%20past%20two%20decades%2C%20per%20Gallup%2C%20even%20if%20the%20amount%20they%20drink%20hasn't%20changed%20much.%20The%20polling%20also%20suggests%20that%20the%20proportion%20of%20Americans%20who%20consume%20alcohol%20has%20for%20decades%20remained%20relatively%20stable%2C%20at%20about%20six%20in%2010.%20Per-capita%20consumption%20of%20ethanol%20from%20alcoholic%20beverages%20has%20stayed%20at%20about%202%20to%202.5%20gallons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20just%20a%20lot%20of%20evidence%20that%20suggests%20even%20though%20we%20have%20more%20alternatives%20than%20ever%2C%20people%20are%20still%20happy%20to%20consume%20and%20indulge%20in%20something%2C%20especially%20if%20they%20feel%20they%20can%20do%20it%20responsibly%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Bryan%20Roth%2C%20the%20director%20of%20insights%20at%20Sightlines%2C%20an%20analyst%20group%20that%20covers%20the%20alcohol%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20some%20people%2C%20drinking%20responsibly%20means%20strategically%20turning%20alcohol%20time%20on%20and%20off%20%E2%80%94%20sometimes%20throughout%20the%20year%20or%20week%2C%20sometimes%20just%20in%20a%20night%20%E2%80%94%20and%20moderating%20without%20giving%20up%20the%20bottle%20entirely.%20They%20think%20it's%20healthier%2C%20even%20if%20their%20doctor%20might%20not%20entirely%20agree.%20It's%20a%20way%20to%20slow%20down%2C%20to%20get%20a%20check%20on%20how%20much%20they're%20drinking.%20And%20sometimes%20they%20just%20can't%20afford%20to%20be%20too%20hungover%20ahead%20of%20a%20big%20workday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20all%20people%20who%20were%20buying%20Athletic%20beers%20and%20Bud%20Zeros%20were%20100%25%20sober%2C%20that%20would%20be%20one%20thing%2C%20but%20what%20we%20find%20is%20a%20good%20majority%20of%20people%20are%20sort%20of%20mixing%20and%20matching%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Nadine%20Sarwat%2C%20an%20analyst%20who%20covers%20the%20beverage%20and%20cannabis%20industries%20at%20Bernstein.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20people%20set%20rules%20for%20themselves%20about%20when%20alcohol%20is%20allowed.%20They%20eschew%20alcohol%20on%20weekdays%20and%20leave%20it%20only%20for%20the%20weekends%20%E2%80%94%20so%20they'll%20drink%20alcoholic%20beer%20on%20a%20Friday%20but%20a%20nonalcoholic%20beer%20at%20lunch%20on%20a%20Wednesday.%20Or%20they'll%20replace%20that%20bottle%20of%20cabernet%20with%20a%200%25%20option%20a%20few%20nights%20a%20week%20to%20take%20it%20easy.%20Some%20drinkers%20take%20part%20in%20Damp%20January%20and%20reduce%20their%20alcohol%20intake%20instead%20of%20going%20totally%20dry.%20Or%20there%20are%20those%20who%20attempt%20a%20harder%20and%20longer%20reset%20with%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F75-hard-tiktok-challenge-safe-mental-toughness-weight-loss-2022-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3B75%20Hard%26quot%3B%20challenge%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20says%20no%20alcohol%20(or%20cheat%20meals%2C%20or%2C%20seemingly%2C%20fun)%20for%2075%20days.%20(There's%20a%20%26quot%3B75%20Soft%26quot%3B%20for%20those%20who%20want%20some%20semblance%20of%20joy.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDay%20to%20day%2C%20at%20the%20bar%20or%20a%20party%2C%20some%20drinkers%20are%20doing%20what's%20been%20dubbed%20%26quot%3Bzebra%20striping%2C%26quot%3B%20where%20they%20alternate%20between%20alcoholic%20and%20nonalcoholic%20beverages%20%E2%80%94%20a%20Manhattan%20one%20round%20and%20a%20mocktail%20the%20next.%20It's%20a%20more%20festive%20%E2%80%94%20albeit%20expensive%20%E2%80%94%20tactic%20than%20chugging%20a%20glass%20of%20water%20between%20drinks.%20In%20other%20instances%2C%20they%20incorporate%20%26quot%3Bbookending%2C%26quot%3B%20where%20they%20begin%20and%20end%20the%20night%20with%20an%20NA%20option.%20Or%20they%20go%20NA%20for%20the%20%26quot%3Bfourth%20quarter%2C%26quot%3B%20finishing%20off%20the%20night%20with%20a%20few%20alcohol-free%20drinks%2C%20emulating%20what%20stadiums%20do%20toward%20the%20end%20of%20sporting%20events.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20then%20becomes%20a%20method%20of%20pacing%20so%20you%20can%20just%20kind%20of%20maintain%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Joaqu%C3%ADn%20Sim%C3%B3%2C%20the%20global%20brand%20ambassador%20and%20mixologist%20for%20On%20the%20Rocks%20Cocktails.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20I%20am%20hearing%20anecdotally%20a%20lot%20more%20too%20is%20just%20people%20who%20are%20like%2C%20'Yeah%2C%20I%20know%20I%20have%20to%20tone%20it%20down%2C%20but%20I%20don't%20want%20to%20give%20it%20up%20entirely.%20So%20I'm%20doing%20this%20as%20a%20means%20of%20dipping%20my%20toes%20not%20necessarily%20into%20sobriety%20but%20more%20into%20temperance.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKaleigh%20Theriault%2C%20an%20associate%20director%20of%20beverage-alcohol%20thought%20leadership%20at%20NIQ%2C%20said%20that%20while%20nonalcoholic%20options%20appeal%20to%20people%20of%20many%20ages%20in%20many%20locations%2C%20higher-income%20people%20tend%20to%20favor%20them.%20Even%20as%20young%20people%20drink%20less%20overall%20and%20look%20for%20more%20ways%20to%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-sober-non-alcoholic-economy-restaurants-events-boom-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebooze-free%20fun%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20many%20are%20still%20imbibing.%20That%20NA%20IPA%20is%20combined%20with%20an%208%25%20IPA%20that%20will%20knock%20their%20socks%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20we%20see%20with%20Gen%20Z%20is%20they%20want%20non-alc%2C%20but%20they%20also%20want%20those%20high-ABV%20beers%20as%20well%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20strongest%20indicator%20that%20someone%20will%20be%20into%20an%20NA%20option%20is%20that%20they're%20also%20an%20alcohol%20drinker%2C%20or%20at%20least%20a%20buyer.%20(Some%20proportion%20of%20NA%20purchasers%20are%20probably%20buying%20for%20parties%20and%20gatherings%20for%20other%20people%20to%20drink.)%20That%20many%20NA%20drinkers%20would%20also%20be%20alcohol%20drinkers%20tracks.%20If%20you%20don't%20really%20have%20a%20taste%20for%20alcohol%2C%20you%20might%20spring%20for%20a%20fun%20mocktail%20from%20time%20to%20time%2C%20but%20you%20may%20also%20just%20go%20with%20a%20Diet%20Coke%2C%20which%20you%20like%20better%2C%20has%20fewer%20calories%2C%20and%20is%20cheaper.%20And%20if%20you've%20never%20been%20a%20beer%20drinker%2C%20you're%20probably%20not%20jazzed%20about%20downing%20an%20NA%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNo%20one%20likes%20the%20taste%20of%20beer%20when%20they%20first%20drink%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Sarwat%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20that's%20a%20universal%20truth.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20people%20who%20have%20given%20up%20drinking%2C%20NA%20options%20can%20be%20appealing%2C%20especially%20as%20the%20offerings%20get%20better%20in%20stores%20and%20at%20restaurants%20and%20bars.%20But%20as%20Laura%20Silverman%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20Zero%20Proof%20Nation%2C%20which%20is%20dedicated%20to%20the%20NA-beverage%20industry%2C%20told%20me%2C%20some%20people%20who%20have%20experienced%20problem%20drinking%20may%20opt%20to%20steer%20clear%20of%20them%20as%20they%20work%20on%20their%20sobriety.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20people%20who%20have%20had%20problems%20with%20alcohol%2C%20many%20doctors%20and%20psychiatrists%20and%20stuff%2C%20they%20recommend%20not%20going%20down%20the%20path%20of%20some%20of%20these%20nonalcoholic%20beverages%20because%20they%20can%20be%20triggering%20for%20some%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20it's%20completely%20individualized.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20also%20a%20divide%20in%20the%20types%20of%20nonalcoholic%20beverages%20people%20are%20consuming%20%E2%80%94%20some%20categories%20are%20doing%20better%20than%20others.%20Most%20of%20the%20analysts%20and%20people%20in%20the%20industry%20I%20talked%20to%20for%20this%20story%20said%20NA%20beer%20was%20pretty%20good%20and%20close%20enough%20to%20the%20real%20thing%20price-wise%20that%20it's%20compelling%20to%20swap%20in.%20Many%20were%20not%20so%20bullish%20about%20wine%20and%20cocktails%20%E2%80%94%20Sim%C3%B3%20said%20that%20besides%20the%20sparkling%20options%2C%20most%20NA%20wine%20was%20%26quot%3Bnot%20good%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20he%20described%20NA%20distillates%20as%20%26quot%3Bhot%20trash.%26quot%3B%20Silverman%20was%20more%20optimistic%20about%20the%20taste%20and%20price%20points.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhere%20we%20were%20before%2C%20everything%20was%20sort%20of%20premium%20because%20it%20was%20the%20only%20thing%20that%20was%20available%2C%26quot%3B%20Silverman%20said.%20%26quot%3BNot%20everything%20has%20an%20exorbitant%20price%20point%20anymore%2C%20but%20there%20is%20a%20wide%20range%2C%20and%20some%20things%20are%20quite%20expensive.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20whole%2C%20Americans%20aren't%20drinking%20markedly%20less%20than%20they%20were%20in%20the%20past%2C%20but%20they%20are%20drinking%20differently.%20Some%20of%20the%20divides%20and%20distinctions%20are%20complicated%20to%20parse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGallup%20has%20found%20that%20while%20young%20people%20report%20drinking%20less%20than%20previous%20generations%20did%2C%20older%20people%20report%20drinking%20more.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-sober-non-alcoholic-economy-restaurants-events-boom-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGen%20Z%20is%2C%20for%20now%2C%20straighter-edged%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20the%20generations%20before%20them%20in%20terms%20of%20alcohol%2C%20but%20that%20doesn't%20necessarily%20amount%20to%20%26quot%3Bthe%20kids%20will%20be%20saints%20forever.%26quot%3B%20With%20marijuana%20legal%20in%20so%20many%20states%2C%20some%20may%20be%20opting%20for%20cannabis%20products%20instead.%20Drinking%20is%20a%20social%20activity%2C%20and%20as%20young%20people%20socialize%20less%2C%20they%20skip%20out%20on%20imbibing%2C%20too.%20Many%20Gen%20Zers%20are%20still%20under%20the%20legal%20drinking%20age%2C%20and%20their%20consumption%20habits%20might%20change%20once%20they're%20not%20breaking%20the%20law.%20Roth%2C%20from%20Sightlines%2C%20told%20me%20that%20so%20far%2C%20as%20Gen%20Zers%20hit%2021%2C%20they%20appear%20to%20be%20drinking%20about%20the%20same%20amount%20millennials%20did%20when%20they%20got%20into%20their%2020s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20we%20see%20younger%20people%20do%20in%20terms%20of%20their%20attitudes%20toward%20drinking%20is%20very%20in%20line%20with%20how%20adults%20are%20shifting%20their%20attitudes%20and%20thought%20processes%20toward%20it%20as%20well%2C%26quot%3B%20Roth%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20just%20a%20greater%20understanding%20of%20how%20it%20impacts%20you.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConsumers%20have%20more%20options%20now%20for%20drinking%20than%20ever.%20A%20lot%20of%20those%20options%20are%20concentrated%20at%20the%20bottom%20and%20at%20the%20top%2C%20with%20a%20sort%20of%20hollowing%20out%20of%20the%20middle.%20Instead%20of%20a%204.2%25%20ABV%20Bud%20Light%2C%20they're%20going%20for%20a%200%25%20Athletic%20or%20a%209%25%20Voodoo%20Ranger%20IPA.%20Or%20they're%20swapping%20a%20six-pack%20of%20Miller%20Lite%20for%20a%20martini%20that%20really%20packs%20a%20punch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDemand%20is%20gravitating%20either%20to%20the%20high%20end%20of%20the%20ABV%20spectrum%20or%20the%20zero-ABV%20spectrum%2C%26quot%3B%20Infante%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20younger%20and%20older%20generations%20alike%20are%20thinking%20about%20their%20habits%20and%20choices%20%E2%80%94%20maybe%20never%20drinking%2C%20or%20maybe%20opting%20in%20sometimes%20and%20out%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20do%20see%20this%20broader%20trend%20of%20moderation%20happening%20across%20the%20industry%2C%26quot%3B%20Theriault%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20ideal%2C%20healthiest%20world%2C%20Americans%20would%20probably%20give%20up%20on%20drinking%2C%20perhaps%20except%20for%20the%20%3Cem%3Emost%20special%20%3C%2Fem%3Eoccasions%20(and%20even%20the%20surgeon%20general%20would%20likely%20say%20that's%20a%20no-no).%20We'd%20also%20have%20a%20perfectly%20balanced%20diet%20of%20fiber%20and%20proteins%20and%20get%20in%20those%2010%2C000%20steps%20a%20day%20plus%20strength%20training%20and%20eight%20hours%20of%20sleep.%20But%20we%20do%20not%20live%20in%20the%20ideal%2C%20healthiest%20world%3B%20we%20live%20in%20the%20real%20one%2C%20where%20drinking%20is%20not%20going%20to%20%26quot%3Bpoof!%26quot%3B%20disappear.%20Part-time%20sober%20%E2%80%94%20or%20mindful%20drinking%20or%20whatever%20you%20want%20to%20call%20it%20%E2%80%94%20might%20be%20the%20best%20some%20people%20can%20do%2C%20or%20are%20at%20least%20willing%20to%20do%2C%20right%20now.%20And%20in%20an%20alcohol%20market%20that's%20increasingly%20split%20between%20super%20sober%20and%20hella%20boozy%2C%20it's%20an%20understandable%20impulse.%20That%20lunchtime%20beer%20was%20never%20a%20good%20idea%20anyway%20%E2%80%94%20let%20alone%20the%20lunchtime%20martini.%20Swap%20it%20out%20for%20a%20Heineken%200.0%20or%20a%20mocktail%2C%20and%20leave%20the%20good%20stuff%20for%20Friday%20night.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Femily-stewart%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EEmily%20Stewart%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider%2C%20writing%20about%20business%20and%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdry-january-sober-alcohol-drinking-beer-cocktails-liquor-gen-z-2025-1%5C%22%3EBusiness