lth%2C%20or%20a%20tax%20on%20resources%2C%20like%20a%20carbon%20tax.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falaska-permanent-fund-basic-income%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAlaska%20Permanent%20Fund%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20for%20example%2C%20gives%20residents%20an%20annual%20stipend%20that's%20drawn%20from%20the%20state's%20oil%20revenue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrue%20UBI%20hasn't%20been%20implemented%20in%20the%20US%2C%20but%20some%20politicians%20have%20introduced%20basic-income%20policies.%20During%20his%20campaign%20for%20the%202020%20Democratic%20primaries%2C%20the%20former%20presidential%20candidate%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fandrew-yangs-on-universal-basic-income-versus-higher-wages-2021-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAndrew%20Yang%3C%2Fa%3E%20proposed%20a%20%26quot%3BFreedom%20Dividend%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20would've%20given%20%241%2C000%20monthly%20to%20every%20American%20over%20the%20age%20of%2018.%20The%202020%20census%20found%20there%20were%20about%20258%20million%20Americans%20over%2018%2C%20which%20would've%20made%20the%20total%20gross%20cost%20of%20that%20plan%20more%20than%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ubicenter.org%2Fwhat-is-ubi%2Fwhy-not-ubi%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DUBI%2520would%2520be%2520expensive%2Cfederal%2520revenues%2520total%2520%25243.5%2520trillion%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%243%20trillion%3C%2Fa%3E%20each%20year.%20Yang%20suggested%20the%20dividend%20be%20funded%20through%20a%20value-added%20retail%20tax.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20comparison%2C%20the%20Social%20Security%20Administration%20reported%20in%202024%20that%20the%20benefits%20cost%20%241.5%20trillion%20annually.%20The%20average%20monthly%20payments%20were%20%241%2C788%20in%20November%20and%20are%20largely%20funded%20through%20payroll%20taxes.%20Seventy-two%20million%20older%20adults%20and%20people%20with%20disabilities%20currently%20receive%20benefits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAny%20federal%20change%20to%20the%20social%20safety%20net%20would%20also%20need%20congressional%20approval.%20Many%20Republican%20leaders%20have%20opposed%20implementing%20ongoing%20basic%20income%2C%20arguing%20that%20it's%20not%20financially%20sustainable%20and%20gives%20people%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguaranteed-basic-income-ban-ubi-arizona-texas-houston-homelessness-poverty-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efree%20money%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20were%20never%20designed%20to%20have%20the%20federal%20government%20supply%20a%20salary%2C%26quot%3B%20Rep.%20John%20Gillette%20of%20the%20Arizona%20House%20of%20Representatives%20previously%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22299dbd34-7ec3-483f-8154-08279638b8ac%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EIs%20UBI%20a%20better%20alternative%20to%20welfare%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20most%20of%20America's%20basic-income%20pilots%2C%20cash%20aid%20is%20seen%20as%20a%20supplement%20to%20welfare%20programs%2C%20not%20a%20replacement.%20GBI%20pilot%20leaders%20often%20consult%20with%20participants%20to%20ensure%20their%20basic%20income%20will%20not%20disqualify%20them%20from%20means-tested%20programs%20like%20SNAP%20or%20Medicaid.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBasic-income%20participants%20have%20told%20BI%20that%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbasic-income-parents-afford-childcare-get-stable-jobs-gbi-ubi-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecash%20helps%20them%20afford%20essentials%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20might%20not%20be%20covered%20by%20traditional%20safety%20nets%3A%20such%20as%20a%20new%20crib%20for%20their%20baby%2C%20school%20supplies%20for%20their%20kids%2C%20steady%20childcare%2C%20and%20car%20repairs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnyone%20who's%20had%20a%20child%20knows%20that%20this%20is%20not%20like%20a%20luxury%20income%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20new%20mom%20in%20Michigan%20receiving%20%24500%20a%20month%20previously%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BThis%20